Source: sauerbraten
Section: games
Priority: optional
Maintainer: GetDeb Package Ninjas <package.ninjas@getdeb.net>
Uploaders: Bruno "Fuddl" Kleinert <fuddl@debian.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9),
               libsdl1.2-dev,
               libsdl-image1.2-dev,
               libsdl-mixer1.2-dev,
               zlib1g-dev,
               imagemagick
Standards-Version: 3.9.3
Homepage: http://sauerbraten.org/

Package: sauerbraten
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         ${shlibs:Depends},
         sauerbraten-data (>= ${sauerbraten-data-ver})
Recommends: sauerbraten-wake6
Description: 3D first-person game engine
 Sauerbraten is a networked fast-paced 3D first-person shooter game. It supports
 rather modern graphic effects and a some nice graphic details.
 .
 The game client also works as the map editor. It is even possible to create 
 and/or edit a map together with other people over a network connection.
 .
 Sauerbraten might be considered unsuitable for children.
 .
 This package installs the game client and map editor.

